						<h1>Sam Lucas</h1>
						<h5>Firefighter, EMT</h5>
						<span class=norm>
						<strong>Age:</strong> 46<br>
						<br>
						<strong>Years on the job:</strong> 4<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What made you decide to become a Fireman?</strong><br>
						Sam Lucas a firefighter/EMT with the Chicago Fire Department remembers when he was a kid in grade school that all the “cool dads” were the dads who were firemen.  But the real
						credit for becoming a fireman should be given to his grandfather whom he is named after.  “My grandfather saved several people from a fire in 1954 at a company based in 			
						Chicago around North and Clybourn.”  “My grandfather unfortunately was not able to save himself.”  Lucas’ father was crushed by the loss.  “My father was not exactly excited 
						by the prospect of me becoming a firefighter.”  Lucas honored his father’s wishes up until four years ago when his father passed away.  He accepted a position with the Chicago				
						Fire Department three years ago.  “I am sure he would be proud of me today.”<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What’s the bravest thing you’ve ever done?</strong><br>
						Being one of the first of twelve men in the history of the Chicago Fire Department to take my shirt off for both charity and public humiliation!<br>
						<br>
						<strong>Fill in the blanks:</strong> <br> 
						I’d rather have a significant other who makes me laugh rather than one that can cook.<br>
						<br>
						<strong>When you’ve had a tough day at the firehouse what do you do to relax?</strong><br>
						Good cardio workout followed by a nice steam.<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What did you want to be when you grew up?</strong><br>
						Grown up? Ask any woman, men never grow up!<br>
						<br>
						<strong>Name one thing you can’t live without?</strong><br>
						TiVO<br>
						<br>
						<strong>Dive Bar or Night Club?</strong><br>
						Matchbox or Richards on Milwaukee<br>
						<br>
						<strong>Cubs or Sox?</strong><br>
						Cubs<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What’s the one thing you can always find in your refrigerator?</strong><br>
						Coffee, not exactly the breakfast of champions!<br>
						<br>
						<strong>When you’re not dressed in uniform what’s your favorite outfit to dress in?</strong><br>
						Jeans, shorts in the summer, plain T-shirt no logo.<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What makes someone a true Chicagoan?</strong><br>
						Digging yourself or a neighbor out of a parking spot in a true Chicago snowstorm.<br>
						<br>
						<strong>What’s the thing you love most about being a fireman?</strong><br>
						The sincere appreciation we receive from the public.  On a recent EMS run we helped an ailing elderly woman.  Her daughter was so appreciative of our care that she felt 
						compelled to write a letter of thanks.  We were just doing our job.  It’s a good feeling that I can’t imagine happening with many other careers out there.
						<br>
